
New York native and CarnegieMellon postdoctoral fellow Larry Bogad specializes in political theatre, a genre closely associated with his Theatre and Dance course Satire, Irony, and Protest. Bogad is an experienced actor, activist, director, and playwright. He is the author of numerous journalpublished articles, as well as the Routledgepublished Electoral Guerrilla Theatre: Radical Ridicule and Social Movements. He holds an M.A. and Ph.D. in Performance Studies from Northwestern University and a B.A. in history from the University of Pennsylvania.

